(132, 1, '2018-09-10 01:59:33', '2018-09-09 22:59:33', 'Paris, this city causes a lot of associations for every person, whether he was there or just wants to visit. The Eiffel tower, the Champs Elysees, croissants, Haute Couture, tennis and football tournaments, beauty and avant – garde, tradition and innovation-all combine one of the largest and most visited cities in the world.\r\n\r\nTo visit Paris, you do not need special occasions or anniversaries – the capital of France is ready for everyone to discover its most attractive features – lovers and businessmen, families with children and single travelers living in luxury hotels and visitors to numerous hostels. At any time of the year you need to go to Paris to recharge your batteries and inspiration for new achievements and creativity.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Trip to France', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '123-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-09-10 01:59:33', '2018-09-09 22:59:33', '', 123, 'http://mynomadtales.com/123-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(133, 1, '2018-09-10 01:59:49', '2018-09-09 22:59:49', 'Munich is the capital of Bavaria, Germany\'s largest Federal state. Bavarians lovingly preserve their culture and traditions. On national holidays, in particular, during the Oktoberfest, residents of the city wear national clothes: men wear leather trousers, and women wear the national dress with the dirndl apron.\r\n\r\nThe first mention of the city dates back to 1158, it was also known as Villa Munichen. In 1175 Munich was granted city status and was walled. The origin of the name of the city comes from the old German mönche (monks), as legend has it that the city was founded by Benedictine monks.\r\n\r\nMunich is a city of museums (46) and art galleries (70). They are the works of the great masters of Europe of XVIII - XIX centuries, such as dürer, Rembrandt, Rubens and Leonardo da Vinci. This wealth brought to the city of Louis I of Bavaria, who founded the most beautiful museums of the city — old and new Pinakothek and the Glyptothek.\r\n\r\nOne of the most important attractions in Munich are The German theatre Museum, which collects and stores the entire history of the Munich theatre, BMW Museum, telling about one of the most popular car brands, the German Museum – Europe\'s largest technical and world-famous English Park.', 'A guide to Europe', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '119-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-09-10 01:59:49', '2018-09-09 22:59:49', '', 119, 'http://mynomadtales.com/119-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(134, 1, '2018-09-10 02:00:02', '2018-09-09 23:00:02', 'Johannesburg (persistent. Johannesburg [dʒoʊˈhænɪsbɜrɡ], Africa. Johannesburg [joˈhɑnəsbʏrx], Zulu iGoli, Kosa iRhawutini) - the largest city in South Africa in terms of population. Locals call it" Joburg"," Jozi "and"Egoli". Johannesburg is the center of Gauteng province, the richest province in South Africa. In 2010, the world Cup matches were held in Johannesburg.\r\n\r\nThe population of the municipality at the end of 2011 was 4 434 827 inhabitants[4], and the whole agglomeration — 7 860 781 people. However, if we consider the surroundings of the metropolis, the population exceeds eight million inhabitants.\r\n\r\nThe territory subordinated to the city is quite large. Johannesburg in the South-West is directly adjacent to the city of Soweto, which is home to a large number of migrants and seasonal workers.\r\n\r\nIn 2000, a new administrative unit, the Johannesburg city district, was formed from the city of Johannesburg and the surrounding areas.\r\n\r\nIn Johannesburg is the constitutional Court of South Africa.\r\n\r\nIn 2002, the city hosted a summit on sustainable development. Johannesburg is the center of large-scale trade in gold and diamonds, which are mined in the surrounding mountains.', 'Travel in Africa', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '115-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-09-10 02:00:02', '2018-09-09 23:00:02', '', 115, 'http://mynomadtales.com/115-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(135, 1, '2018-09-10 02:00:15', '2018-09-09 23:00:15', 'Sydney-the capital of the Australian state Of new South Wales, colorful and diverse, the largest and oldest city in Australia located in the South-East of the country. Sydney was founded on 26 January 1788 by Arthur Philip, head of the first party of British colonists, and named after the English Minister of the interior Lord Sydney. It was granted city status on July 20, 1842.\r\n\r\nSydney offers a huge number of excursions and entertainment for every taste, there is everything - and the noisy fun of the big city and unity with wildlife, and a great beach holiday. No city in the world can compare to Sydney in the number of beaches scattered around it.\r\n\r\nSurrounded by beaches, mountains and parks, Sydney has something to attract tourists. But apparently not only its natural beauty is famous for Sydney, once he managed to turn from a convict settlement of the 17th century in the economic and cultural center of the 21st century, receiving more than 2.6 million tourists a year.', 'Adventure in Australia', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '111-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-09-10 02:00:15', '2018-09-09 23:00:15', '', 111, 'http://mynomadtales.com/111-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(136, 1, '2018-09-10 02:00:30', '2018-09-09 23:00:30', 'Africa-the second largest continent after Eurasia, is washed by the Mediterranean sea from the North, Red-from the North-East, the Atlantic ocean from the West and the Indian ocean from the East and South. Africa is also called part of the world, consisting of the continent of Africa and the surrounding Islands. The area of Africa without Islands is 29.2 million km2, with Islands — about 30.3 million km2[3], thus covering 6% of the total surface area of the Earth and 20.4% of the land surface. There are 55 States in Africa.\r\n\r\nAfrica has a population of about a billion people. Africa is considered the ancestral home of mankind: it is here that the oldest remains of early hominids and their probable ancestors were found, including the sahelanthropus, Avstralopitecus africanus , A. afarensis, Homo erectus, H. habilis and H. ergaster.\r\n\r\nThe African continent crosses the equator and several climatic zones; it is the only continent stretching from the Northern subtropical climatic zone to the southern subtropical. Due to lack of regular precipitation and irrigation as well as glaciers or mountain aquifer systems — the natural regulation of the climate anywhere except the coasts, is practically not observed.', 'Travel to Africa', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '107-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-09-10 02:00:30', '2018-09-09 23:00:30', '', 107, 'http://mynomadtales.com/107-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
